games.comment: Brett Favre turned into a touchdown. Unfortunately, New York failed on its 2.point conversion. If Chad Pennington could have scored a touchdown at the end of the contest, Miami would have won, 21-20.    The big news in this game was Brett Favre. Favre's arm strength was apparent in his 15-of-22 for 194 yards and 2 touchdown performance. However, he fumbled twice. That said, Favre's a huge upgrade over Chad Pennington, no matter what

Brett Favre left the game with a shoulder injury and the Bills immediately went up 7-0, I wrote the following in the forum: Looks like I'll be losing 2 units because of the Favre injury. Sucks. Whoops. All Minnesota did after that was reel off 31 consecutive points to close out the half.
